#### text-block ####
text:

In a special joint session of the Planning Commission and Design Review Board, the project received overall praise from city officials and the public, despite many proposed revisions. The *East Bay Times* [reported](http://www.eastbaytimes.com/2016/09/12/el-cerrito-scrutinizes-del-norte-area-mixed-use-proposal/) that some community members described the separation of market-rate and affordable housing as “disappointing,” additionally lamenting the presence of “too much space for parking.”

BRIDGE Housing made note of a completed project built at the Pleasant Hill BART station in a partnership with Holliday. The non-profit agency is also [developing](http://www.bridgehousing.com/what-we-do/macarthur-station) a mixed-use apartment complex next to the MacArthur BART station in Oakland.

The city of El Cerrito recently rezoned the area for higher-density development near transit under the [San Pablo Avenue Specific Plan](http://www.el-cerrito.org/index.aspx?nid=396), adopted in December 2014. The Planning Department designed a [Form-Based Code](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Form-based_code), as well as pedestrian-friendly transit goals, “[i]n order to increase accessibility and livability while increasing land use intensity.”
